<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>newbie: I just want the earth pet, I only got air this level, I can't solo without earth</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Didi: Hm, I always found air to be very good for soloing.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>newbie: so do you have the spells?</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Didi: what spells?<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>newbie: the earth pet</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Didi: um, no, the pets you can't buy are researched, you can't buy them anywhere<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>newbie: can you research them?</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Didi: if you have the components, I can try ... you can find the list of research on www.magecompendium.com<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>newbie: oh forget it, I'm not interested in that stuff</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Didi: er, okay<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>newbie: so you won't help me</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Didi: I'm perfectly willing to help you, but I can't give you something I don't have<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>newbie: so do you have any cool magic items I can have that'll make me really strong?</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Didi: you keep asking for things I don't have ...<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>newbie: being a mage sucks.  They're so weak.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Didi: actually, mages are very strong.  Excellent soloers and very high damage in groups too.  We can outdamage the warriors with good pets.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>newbie: I keep dying. Mages suck. I need better equipment.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Didi: You could easily earn yourself some money in the grimling mines in Tenebrous Mountains, at your level should not be hard.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>newbie: Is it right beside a zone? People keep taking me places they say are good and then I die.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
&lt;Didi downgrades her estimation of the probably competence of newbie even further, if possible.&gt;<br>
Didi: hm, well, it's not too far, but it's not RIGHT beside the zone.  Maybe somewhere closer would be safer.  How about the bandits in Paludal Caverns?  Not as much money, but it's very convenient and close to a zone, and at this time of night, should not be overcamped.  At 44, no problem making some cash.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>newbie: I was there for 4 levels when I was in my 20s.  They come in bunches and kill me.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Didi: well, I think you'll find that now they're green to you, it will be easier, long as you don't do something silly like sit down in the middle of them...<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>newbie: oh.  but you're an elf. would it be easy for human too?</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Didi: er ... the only difference between our abilities is that dark elves can see in the dark, humans are blind.  It doesn't make me a stronger mage.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>newbie: oh.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Didi: &lt;feeling remarkably generous&gt; Would you like me to come along and stand by while you try it, in case you get into trouble?<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>newbie: I forget where it is, gonna sleep soon I guess, there's no groups</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Didi: perhaps you should consider getting to know a guild or association, so you have some company?<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>newbie: I'll never join a guild.  I'll never belong to a club if I'm not president of it, IRL too.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Didi: well, if you're going to just spend all your time sitting around LFG, maybe you should go farm silks somewhere, then at least you'd make some money while you wait, they sell for 1pp or more in the bazaar.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>newbie: I'll never be a bazaar trader, lag sux.  Can pets use focus items?</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Didi: er, yes.  Your air and water pets both nuke, they can use the damage bracers.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>newbie: air pet sucks, it always disappears before I can give it armour.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Didi: um, if you cast See Invisible on yourself, you can see the air pet<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>newbie: wow, I never knew that!</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
Didi: I find air and water are good pets for kiting, my favorites for soloing<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>newbie: what's kiting?</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Didi: &lt;explanation of kiting, chain pet casting, and necro reverse kiting&gt;<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>newbie: wow kewl I never thought of that.  I got to 44 in 1 month, do you know any mages who did that?</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Didi: that's quite fast.  It certainly took me longer.  Then again, I was doing quests and faction work and other things.  &lt;thinks: like learning to play my class...&gt; But it's certainly speedy.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>newbie: I got to 44 in one month. I'm a total newbie lol.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Didi: &lt;hinting heavily&gt; well, no matter how high level I get, I find there's always lots more to learn about how to play my class<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>newbie: well maybe I try the bandits</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Didi: www.eqatlas.com will show you maps of all the zones and how to get there.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>newbie: kewl thanks everybody on this server is so unfriendly I'll put you on my friends list. I'm going to sleep now.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Didi: &lt;feeling of dread hits&gt; good luck.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>newbie: think I'm gonna make a necro on another server.  Mages are so weak. I hear they're good.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
etc.<br>
<br>
It was actually much longer and more painful than this but I paraphrase for the sake of length.<br>
<br>
